We are looking for Azure Technical Solution Architect in Florida.

 Role: Azure Technical Solution Architect
 

Client: Direct (one of the Fortune 100 Companies)
Location: Boca Raton, FL (3 days in Office)

 Duration: Long term

 

We are seeking a skilled Azure Solutions Architect to lead in our efforts to migrate to and manage our newly implemented Azure environment.


Your responsibilities will include strategizing, designing, implementing and managing our Azure infrastructure and services.
Our ideal candidate will have a solid understanding of cloud computing and technology systems, as well as experience designing and transferring applications to cloud.
You should have a positive attitude and excellent communication skills to effectively share your knowledge.
Duties and responsibilities:
Design and implement cloud architecture using Azure resources
Analyze and evaluate the company’s existing systems and infrastructure to propose improvements
Translate business requirements into secure, scalable, and reliable cloud solutions
Communicate effectively with stakeholders and team members about the cloud architecture and its implications
Coordinate with the cloud operations team to ensure the solution is effectively managed and maintained
Stay updated about the latest developments in cloud computing and Azure platform
Implement automation tools and frameworks for cloud deployments
Ensure the cloud environment meets compliance requirements and follow best security practices
Provide technical guidance and support for cloud development teams
Identify, analyze, and resolve infrastructure vulnerabilities and application deployment issues
Plan, organize, and control multiple responsibilities and resources to achieve project objectives.
Qualifications and Skills :
Proven work experience as a Solutions Architect or similar software engineering role.
Expert knowledge and experience of
Management group, subscriptions, resource groups etc
Storage solutions with Files, Blobs, SQL , CosmosDB
Infrastructure solutions with VM, Batch, App service, Azure functions, LogicApps, Container instances, Kubernetes Service
Other Azure components e.g API management, KeyVaults, Event Hubs, Message Bus
Implemented Microsoft Well Architected Framework Pillars of Cost, Operational Efficiency, Performance ,Reliability and Security
Good problem-solving skills and ability to think logically.
 

BSc degree in Computer Science, Engineering or relevant field; MSc degree will be preferred.


Nice to have: Microsoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect Expert

 

 

 

